Nigerian televangelist Timothy Omotoso appeared in the Port Elizabeth Magistrates Court on Friday morning. CAPE TOWN - A Durban-based pastor at the centre of a sexual assault case has been denied bail for the second time.Nigerian televangelist Timothy Omotoso appeared in the Port Elizabeth Magistrates Court on Friday morning.He's alleged to have recruited and groomed young girls for sex at his church.The Port Elizabeth Magistrates Court has found Omotoso's lawyers have not brought new facts to support his second bail bid.The 58-year-old will, therefore, remain in custody.The accused allegedly trafficked young girls and women from various branches of his church across South Africa.He was arrested by the Hawks at Port Elizabeth Airport in April.The Nigerian pastor denies all allegations against him.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)